main event: One round object was observed in the sky over St. Augustine, Florida on July 31, 1956.
interesting points: The object was described as round and comparable in size to a softball., It was white or silver in color., The object was observed at a very high altitude (85 degrees elevation) for 1 hour and 20 minutes., Observers used binoculars of unknown power to view the object., The sighting is being recorded as a possible balloon due to insufficient data.
witness description: Civilian source, no specific witnesses noted.
